%section
  %h2 Introduction
  %p
    Keyserver tracks software usage on Penn Libraries public computers.
    Events and sessions are captured from Keyserver's raw tables and loaded into Metridoc.
    Individual usernames are visible only to super admins.
  %ul
    %li
      The
      %strong Software Usage
      page lists all managed products with checkout activity on non-staff computers,
      including status (Active / Stale / Dormant) based on days since the last checkout.
    %li
      The
      %strong Stale &amp; Dormant
      page surfaces products with no checkout in 90+ days, sorted by most dormant first.
    %li
      The
      %strong Locations
      page shows session heatmaps by hour of day and day of week, broken down by library location.
    %li
      The
      %strong By School
      page shows checkout counts per product per Alma school affiliation.
    %li
      The
      %strong By User Group
      page shows checkout counts per product per Alma user group (e.g. undergraduate, graduate, faculty).

%hr

%section
  %h2 Resources
  %h3 Database Access
  %p{:style => "padding: 0px 0px 0px 30px;"}
    For those who are connecting directly to the PostgreSQL database or who are
    using the report exporting tool, the tables for Keyserver data
    begin with the prefix "keyserver_".

  %h3 Data Tables
  %ul
    - resources.each do |resource|
      %li= link_to resource.resource_name.human, resource.route_collection_path

