%section
  %h2 Data Import

  %h3 File Upload
  %p
    Events and sessions data can be loaded directly through the
    = link_to "File Upload Tool", admin_tools_file_upload_imports_path
  %ol
    %li
      Export the events or sessions data from Keyserver as
      %code .xlsx
      or
      %code .csv
      \.
    %li
      In the File Upload Tool, select the target table (
      %strong Keyserver Event
      or
      %strong Keyserver Session
      ) and upload the file.
    %li
      Abbreviated column headers (e.g.
      %code name
      ,
      %code user
      ,
      %code event
      ) are mapped to database columns automatically.
    %li Session length is derived from logon/logoff on import, so any Duration column in the file is ignored.
    %li Duplicate records are handled on the backend; re-uploading a file that has already been imported is safe.

  %h3 Rake Import
  %p
    To load data via the command line, export
    %code events.xlsx
    and
    %code sessions.xlsx
    from itam_db into
    %code /tmp/keyserver/
    then run:
  %pre rake import -- --config_folder keyserver
